Maintainer: Alp Toker <alp@atoker.com>
Standards-Version: 3.5.6
Build-Depends: debhelper (>> 3.0.0), libglib2.0-dev, bison

Package: mono-jit
Provides: cli-virtual-machine
Architecture: i386
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, mono-assemblies, mono-common (= ${Source-Version})
Description: a .NET runtime environment
 The Mono Project is an open development initiative sponsored by Ximian that is
 working to develop an open source, Linux-based version of the Microsoft .NET
 development platform. Its objective is to enable Linux developers to build and
 deploy cross-platform .NET Applications. The project will implement various
 technologies developed by Microsoft that have now been submitted to the ECMA
 for standardization.

